I want to thank everyone who came out to one of my shows on this tour. The Sun and Moon project is something that has been on my mind for awhile and i‚Äôm really happy with how it turned out, and i‚Äôm stoked to bridge the 2 styles of music I love to produce together. thank you for supporting my musical journey thus far. i‚Äôll be taking a touring hiatus for a while now, and focusing on more production. to be totally transparent, i‚Äôve struggled for the past few years to put out new music and projects due to touring so much. I love playing shows, but it‚Äôs definitely worn on me. it‚Äôs not all sunshine and rainbows and a party. it‚Äôs hard work, sleepless nights on the road, long nights in the studio, compromising of eating healthy food and cooking at home, living out of a suitcase, 6am flights to the next city for another show, etc etc the list goes on. but it‚Äôs all been worth it ‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è I love the music, and i‚Äôm here for that not for the party. the music, the community, and the people are what has carried me through the journey of this music industry. i‚Äôll be back next year sometime to play select shows, but expect a lot more music from me, and i‚Äôm hoping it‚Äôs my best work yet üòò the Sun and Moon album is dropping shortly (after project and DAW issues it‚Äôs now finished) .
